		    <div class="container text-center py-4"><h2><b>Where Early Years Matter</b></h2></div>
			
    <div class="container-fluid">
	    <div class="row">
		<div class="col-xl-1"></div>
		<div class="col-lg-5 col-xl-4 pb-4">

			PIPS is an international kindergarten with five campuses across Hong Kong. Our Hong Kong Island,  Kowloon and LOHAS campuses teach the IB Primary Years Programme (PYP), while our Rhine Garden campuses follow local curriculum, catering to the diverse needs of families in Hong Kong. Our facilities serve children aged 1 to 6. Our team of highly qualified educators, possessing extensive expertise in early childhood education, is dedicated to fostering a secure, nurturing, and stimulating environment that cultivates globally aware young learners.<br><br>
 
At PIPS, our classes provide children with the opportunity to engage in a bilingual/trilingual environment, guided by two classroom teachers who instruct in their native languages. Additionally, we nurture children’s appreciation for the arts through sessions led by our music specialists, enhance early literacy development in our well-equipped library, and promote physical development through activities in our spacious outdoor playground.<br><br> 
 
PIPS adopts an inquiry- and play-based approach to education. We firmly believe that children thrive through meaningful interactions and practical experiences. This dynamic curriculum is supported by our innovative learning environment and the integration of information and communication technology (ICT). 
		</div>
	
	
